author: Inside Edition
description: When she was just 22-years-old, Brigitte Bardot became a global sex symbol. The French beauty oozed sexuality in the movie "And God Created Woman." After starring in more than 40 films, Bardot stepped away from the film industry and devoted her life to promoting animal rights. In her later decades, however, she mired herself in far-right politics, and was credited with Islamophobic statements.
title: French Actress Brigitte Bardot Dies At 91

author: Inside Edition
description: The mystery deepens in the urgent search for 19-year-old Camila Mendoza Olmes, who disappeared on Christmas Eve. Authorities now claim she is in "imminent danger." The investigation includes several possibilities. Could Camila be a victim of human trafficking? Was she kidnapped? Did she leave on her own accord? The last image of her is a grainy surveillance photo taken not far from her home in San Antonio, Texas, on December 24.
title: Urgent Search For Teen Who Vanished On Christmas Eve

author: Inside Edition
description: The new year may be just around the corner, but fear of terrorism is putting a damper on festivities across the globe. In the wake of the recent horrific attack in Australia's Bondi Beach, the traditional New Year's Eve celebration in Sydney has been cancelled. People in Paris are being told to steer clear of the traditional fireworks display at the Arc de Triomphe, and to watch it live on TV instead. Celebrations in Hong Kong and Tokyo have also been scaled back.
title: Terrorism Fears Put Damper On New Years Celebrations

author: Inside Edition
description: White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt has been keeping a little secret: she's pregnant again. The 28-year-old got decked out in a fitted, white sweater-dress for the holidays, revealing her baby bump on Instagram. It's Leavitt's second child with her real estate developer husband, 60-year-old Nicholas Riccio. When asked about the pregnancy on Fox, Lara Trump hinted that Leavitt's maternity leave would be brief.
title: Will White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt Go On Maternity Leave?

author: Inside Edition
description: Three tons of confetti will rain down on Times Square in just two days. Written on all those colorful pieces of paper will be dreams and wishes for the new year. People lined up for the opportunity to write down their wishes for 2026. Some hoped for health; others for wealth, professional success, or friendship. They dropped their wishes in boxes that will be poured out as a million revellers gather. Others posted their hopes, dreams and desires for 2026 on a wishing wall.
title: There's Something Unusual About This New Year's Confetti

author: Inside Edition
description: A man was captured on surveillance camera shopping at a music store. A gorgeous vintage mandolin on the wall caught his eye. He took a photo of it on his cellphone, and moments later he pulled the instrument from the wall and stuffed it inside his jacket. After looking around, he reached for another mandolin, and stuffed that in his jacket, as well. The brazen theft happened at Lark's Music in Teaneck, New Jersey.
title: Suspect Returns Shoplifted Mandolins

author: Inside Edition
description: A little volcanic eruption wasn't going to stop these winter warriors from enjoying a day on the slopes. Mount Etna is the most active volcano in Italy and started spewing ash just after Christmas. With many people enjoying planned ski trips over the holiday, they chose to go to the mountain anyway. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Skiers Hit The Slopes On Mount Etna During Most Recent Eruption

author: Inside Edition
description: After starting her first company at 23 years old, entrepreneur Kim Perell became a multi-millionaire by the age of 30. Along with running multimillion dollar companies, Perell, a wife, mother and bestselling author, has dedicated her life to empowering the next generation of business leaders. In her new book "Mistakes That Made Me A Millionaire'', Perell shares the secrets to her success for dreaming big. She shared tips with Inside Edition on how to kickstart the new year.
title: Entrepreneur Kim Perell Gives Tips On How To Kickstart New Year

author: Inside Edition
description: Alex wasn't supposed to live past the age of four, but she has defied science.
title: Woman Born 'Without A Brain' Celebrates 20th Birthday #shorts
